Sarcasm

In[19]:
import json
In[20]:
datastore = []

with open("Sarcasm_Headlines_Dataset.json", 'r') as f:
    for line in f:
        # Try to load each line as JSON
        try:
            json_obj = json.loads(line)
            datastore.append(json_obj)
        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
            print("Error decoding JSON:", e)
            continue
In[21]:
sentences = []
labels = []
urls = []
In[22]:
for item in datastore:
    sentences.append(item['headline'])
    labels.append(item['is_sarcastic'])
    urls.append(item['article_link'])

In[70]:

test_size = int(len(padded)*0.1)
In[73]:
train = np.array(sentences[:train_size])
train_labels = np.array(labels[:train_size])

val = np.array(sentences[train_size:train_size + val_size])
val_labels = np.array(labels[train_size:train_size + val_size])

test = np.array(sentences[train_size +val_size:])
test_labels = np.array(labels[train_size +val_size:])

recreate Tokenizer

In[75]:
vocab_size = 10000
embedding_dim = 16
max_length = 100
oov_tok = "<OOV>"
trunc_type='post'
padding_type='post'
In[76]:
tokenizer = Tokenizer(num_words=vocab_size, oov_token=oov_tok)
tokenizer.fit_on_texts(train)

word_index = tokenizer.word_index

train_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(train)
train_padded = pad_sequences(train_sequences, maxlen=max_length, padding=padding_type, truncating=trunc_type)
In[77]:
val_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(val)
val_padded = pad_sequences(val_sequences, maxlen=max_length, padding=padding_type, truncating=trunc_type)
In[79]:
test_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(test)
test_padded = pad_sequences(test_sequences, maxlen=max_length, padding=padding_type, truncating=trunc_type)

Embedding

In[100]:
l2_reg = 0.001  # You can adjust this parameter as needed

model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Embedding(vocab_size, embedding_dim, input_length=max_length),
    tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(24, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=tf.keras.regularizers.l2(l2_reg)),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
In[101]:
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer = 'adam',
             metrics = ['accuracy'])
In[102]:
num_epochs = 15
history = model.fit(train_padded, train_labels, epochs=num_epochs, validation_data=(val_padded, val_labels), verbose=2)

In[118]:
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

embedding_matrix = model.layers[0].get_weights()[0]

# Perform PCA to reduce dimensionality
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
embeddings_2d = pca.fit_transform(embedding_matrix)

# Plot the embeddings
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
for i in range(len(embeddings_2d)):
    plt.text(embeddings_2d[i, 0], embeddings_2d[i, 1], str(i))
plt.xlim(min(embeddings_2d[:, 0]), max(embeddings_2d[:, 0]))
plt.ylim(min(embeddings_2d[:, 1]), max(embeddings_2d[:, 1]))
plt.xlabel('PCA Component 1')
plt.ylabel('PCA Component 2')
plt.title('Word Embeddings')
plt.show()
In[121]:
from sklearn.manifold import TSNE

# Assuming you have a trained embedding layer
embedding_matrix = model.layers[0].get_weights()[0]

# Perform t-SNE to reduce dimensionality
tsne = TSNE(n_components=2)
embeddings_2d = tsne.fit_transform(embedding_matrix)

subsampled_embeddings = embeddings_2d[::10]  # Example: plot every 10th point

# Plot the subsampled embeddings
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.scatter(subsampled_embeddings[:, 0], subsampled_embeddings[:, 1], alpha=0.5)
plt.xlabel('t-SNE Component 1')
plt.ylabel('t-SNE Component 2')
plt.title('Word Embeddings (t-SNE)')
plt.show()
